aws-transcripts.transcript: I've learned some of my most important life lessons from drug dealers and gang members and prostitutes, and I've had some of my most profound theological conversations not in the hallowed halls of a seminary, but on a street corner. The Friday night 1 a.m. That's that's a little unusual since I am a Baptist minister. Seminary trained and passed to the church for over 20 years. But it's true. It came as a part of my participation in a public safety crime reduction strategy that saw a 79% reduction in violent crime over an eight year period in a major city.
